ch-humanistischen Gelehrtenpoesie, welche den Geltungsanspruch der kirchlichen Orthodoxien 'von außen' infragestellt. Humanismus und Mystik bereiten so gleichermaßen der Aufklärung den Boden.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aGerman poetryy18th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aGerman poetryyEarly modern, 1500-1700xHistory and criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies - <1990z9783110637816oZDB-23-GLC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-DITION: BEST OF GERMAN STUDIESz9783110233933oZDB-23-DGH0 cprintz978348410561440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311094062640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110940626423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110940626/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGH  aZDB-23-GLCb1990